Sentencas: A technique for formation of electrolyte thin films with the thickness of 6-10 mu m of zirconia stabilized by yttria (YSZ) is developed on the basis of the method of chemical deposition from the vapor phase of organometallic compounds (MOCVD).
Titulo: Development of Solid-Oxide Fuel Cell for Reduced Operating Temperatures

Sentencas: Planar electrochemical cells based on film electrolyte with a supporting anode with the working surface area of 12 cm(2) were manufactured.
Titulo: Development of Solid-Oxide Fuel Cell for Reduced Operating Temperatures

Sentencas: A solid-oxide fuel cell (SOFC) based on two fuel cells was developed and its life cycle tests at reduced operating temperatures (<800 degrees C) were carried out for 400 h.
Titulo: Development of Solid-Oxide Fuel Cell for Reduced Operating Temperatures

Sentencas: The maximum power density reached in the SOFC tests was 316 mW/cm(2).
Titulo: Development of Solid-Oxide Fuel Cell for Reduced Operating Temperatures
